### Test Authentication Endpoints

### 1. Signup - Register a new user
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 2. Login - Get JWT token
POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 3. Get Current User Info (Protected Route)
GET http://localhost:5000/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### Test Reminder Endpoints (All Protected)

### 4. Create a new reminder (requires authentication)
POST http://localhost:5000/api/reminders
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "medicineName": "Aspirin",
  "time": "08:00 AM",
  "note": "Take with food"
}

### 5. Get all reminders for authenticated user
GET http://localhost:5000/api/reminders
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### 6. Delete a reminder (replace :id with actual reminder ID)
DELETE http://localhost:5000/api/reminders/REMINDER_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

